examples.en: Am I my brother's keeper?
examples.ru: ? (.  - .           "I do not know. Am I my brother's keeper?")

examples.en: Her brother's a real meathead.
Her brother's a complete loony.
Her brother's a real birdbrain.
He bought his brother's business.
My little brother's a real menace.
He seethed at his brother's success.
He wanted to avenge his brother's death.
My brother's studying to be an accountant.
Sarah rejected her brother's offer of help.
Your brother's gone - died half-an-hour ago.
His brother's success left him in the shade.
Carrie slipped her arm through her brother's.
Please stop obtruding in your brother's affairs.
Dad always takes my brother's part when we argue.
He became more withdrawn after his brother's death.
He confided his money to his brother's safekeeping.
Her brother's a bit simple, but he's quite harmless.
Her brother's act was just a wind-up to get her angry.
Hold on a minute! Isn't that your brother's car over there?
He has committed himself to support his brother's children.
The memory of her brother's death is still present in her mind.
William was acting as a surrogate father for his brother's son.
Her brother's success and popularity always made her feel inadequate.
Since we're in the neighborhood, why don't we drop in at my brother's?
His brother's stinking rich (=very rich, in a way that you do not approve of).
He had accidentally disarrayed his brother's CDs, leaving a telltale sign of borrowing without permission.
She rolled her eyes at her brother's bragging and quipped, You're a legend in your own mind, all right.
You need to put some distance between you and your brother's death. *
